Author: jl777c#5810
Content: i dont think the komodo team should be vouching officially for any specific external project. All of these projects are out of the control of komodo team, so they can change at any time. then again, it could be the best new crypto project around. Please research and make your own decisions. Being a tech provider, we can provide the tech, but we cant be put in the position where we are expected to identify all the possible problems with a project. Many projects are run by former (or even existing) team members. Such projects can certainly mention these things. Also, if we find anybody making false claims, we will call them out.

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: in other words we are taking a step back from making formal partnerships, especially since in a decentralized project it doesnt really make sense. that being said, i expect projects will do partnerships, contract work, etc. with the various ecosystem companies

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: I know this doesnt make it as easy as possible to find the investment values, but at least the number isnt so large, it is still possible to research each of them as they arrive

Author: Mister.G#3159
Content: I completely understand and I don't expect you to vouch for anyone that uses the Komodo name. The thing is, if a project claims to have a partnership I assume the best way to identify the validity of this is to a) ask the project making the assertion or b) ask the Komodo team.

Author: Mister.G#3159
Content: I am simply asking whether the paper they have claiming that Komodo is a partner is true or false?

Author: jl777c#5810
